text.tspan: Death rate from obesity vs. share of adults who are obese, 2016
Premature deaths attributed to obesity per 100,000 individuals. Obesity is defined as having a body-mass index
(BMI) equal to, or greater than, 30. BMI is a person's weight (in kilograms) divided by their height (in meters)
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease (2019); WHO, Global Health Observatory
Note: To allow comparisons between countries and over time this metric is age-standardized.
